All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Adjuster
Something implementing adjuster indicates it will adjust and unadjust a character.
Adjustment
Adjustment provides a base implementation for adjusting and unadjusting a character's state.
CanSearchCharacter
Interface that indicates anything that implements it supports opening the search screen for values from a Character
CanSearchRules
Interface that indicates anything that implements it supports opening the search screen for values from the rulebook
Character
A representation of a characters state in a rpg game
Controller
The main controller, in addition to normal controller responsibilities, is also responsible for instantiating all the other controllers, as well as holding some methods for intercontroller communication.
DemoWorld
Holds a set of defaults used for characters using the demo world ruleset, this way the character classes implementation is kept separate from rule specifics.
Dice
Dice Class responsible for managing a single die (singular of "dice").
DiceController
DiceController is responsible for controlling the DicePanel via View and relevant data for the model (RuleBook and Character)
DicePanel
This class represents the view component for rolling dice.
DiceRoller
Responsible for managing rolling the dice pool (2 six-sided dice) required for this game with both, either or neither of the below sub conditions applied: advantage - roll 2 pools and take the highest.
EntryList
This Panel is for a list of entrys that can be selected and a action.
EntryManager<T extends Named>
Manages a collection of Named Entries for example: Feature, Specialty
Experience
The Experience class represents a character's experience and how far they are from hitting a level up.
Feature
A game feature in the game that can include automated adjustments and Requirement that can be checked against implements the Adjuster interface to adjust and unadjust a characters state.
FeatureList
FeatureList that extends EntryList and implements ReliesOnCharacterData.
FeatureSearchController
Responsible for managing the Feature screen and its interactions with the character data model.
GameController
Parent class for any controllers that require access to the full game state.
HasRequirements
Something implementing the HasRequirements interface indicates it can have a list of requirements that may have to be met.
Hitpoints
Hitpoints represents the hitpoints of a Character.
HpPanel
HpPanel extends JPanel and implements ReliesOnCharacterData.
Main
Launch the application GUI.
Main
A main routine to test the model.
MainController
Interface that indicates anything that implements it supports all the functions of a main controller.
MainView
Interface for the Main View
MaxHpAdjustment
This is an implementation for adjusting the maximum Hitpoints of a Character.
MaxXpAdjustment
This is an implementation for adjusting the maximum Experience of a Character.
Menu
Menu Panel that is the default starting page for the program.
MenuBar
MenuBar that extends JMenuBar
MenuBarController
Controller responsible for managing the MenuBar via the View.
MenuController
Controller the Menu Splash Screen
Named
Something implementing the Named interface indicates you can get its name.
Notification
A JFrame that will spawn on the bottom right of the screen acting as an OS-agnostic notification.
PrimaryStat
The PrimaryStat class represents a primary stat of a character.
ReliesOnCharacterData
Something implementing the ReliesOnCharacterData interface indicates it will update itself based on the new character data and pass it on to its relevant children, so they can do the same.
Requirement
Requirements check if a Character has a given Stat that matches the statKey held by this and if that Character Stat is equal to or above the threshold requirement is enforcing.
RuleBook
Abstract class spelling out what a Rulebook will have at the minimum for methods.
Scholar
This class is responsible for loading in a given character sheet file and processing it.
Scholar.Mode
An enum for tracking the current processing mode of the program (NONE, SPECIALTIES, FEATURES).
Scribe
The Scribe class provides functionality to write contents to a file.
Search
Manages presenting a searchable wrapper around a JList that can be searched using a JTextField and a JButton for "picking" a selected option.
Sheet
Sheet extends JPanel implements ReliesOnCharacterData
SheetController
Controller for the Sheet via the View using the RuleBook and Character as our model.
Specialty
A game specialty in the game that holds feautres it can bestow on a character and requirements that can be checked against implements the Adjuster interface to adjust and unadjust a characters state.
SpecialtyList
SpecialtyList that extends EntryList and implements ReliesOnCharacterData.
SpecialtySearchController
Responsible for managing the Specialty screen and its interactions with the character data model.
Stat
Representation of some Named statistic (Stat) of a Character, an object constructed from multiple Values with a name and a description.
StatAdjustment
This is an implementation for adjusting a target Stat of a Character.
StatsPanel
Responsible for displaying the Character current PrimaryStat state
Value
Represents a game Value that has a mininum amount, a maximum amount, and a current amount.
View
View is a JFrame that Implements MainView.
XpPanel
JPanel responsible for displaying the Character current xp score and managing buttons that alter the characters Experience state via the relevant controller.
